n applies. I wonder if MethodHandles.lookup() could work, but reflection complicates things. Direct bytecode generation could be a way forward, yet I'd need to ensure everything compiles without issues.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering test structure changes**\\n\\nI'm contemplating whether to add a test source named `SAXBuilderCoverageAccessor.java` under the `org.jdom.input` package. However, this would violate instructions to keep tests outside of library packages. Even as a helper, it doesn't feel right. Is there a way to create a custom class earlier in the test classpath? I wonder if there's a public API in SAXBuilder that uses a different class literal, but so far, it seems limited. My task is to improve the situation while following the rules, but I’m unsure how to proceed.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Examining runtime initialization options**\\n\\nI'm considering whether to use `RuntimeClassInitialization.initializeAtRunTime(SAXBuilder.class)` in a feature, but that seems too broad and would require build argument changes. Could a test ensure runtime class initialization by referencing the class only after? However, it appears that the native image class initialization policy is set at build time, which complicates things. I'm leaning toward exploring other avenues since this approach may not align with the requirements I have to follow.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_amTK0ZXel3oLgHuHLDjnx9bV|fc_0f7978e24a50aaa60169ef8b3325048190a61abf370e0cb1b0", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "find tests/src -path '*/src/test/resources/META-INF/native-image/*/native-image.properties' -o -path '*/src/main/resources/META-INF/native-image/*/native-image.properties' | head -20 | xargs -r -n1 sh -c 'echo --- $0; head -20 \"$0\"'", "timeout": 10}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1770, "output": 1295, "cacheRead": 45056, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 48121, "cost": {